description.narrative: By 2021, UNICEF and its partners in South Asia are better equipped to effectively develop and apply gender analysis, to deliver gender equitable results for children which contribute to national and international commitments for children, gender equality, and promote the value and empowerment of women and children., which contributes to Technical Excellence In Evaluation, Technical Excellence In Humanitarian Action, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Comprehensive, sustainable and enabling environment that leaves no child behind is supported by policies, programmes, strategies, budgets and actions of Governments, regional institutions, private sector, media, financial institutions, UN and UNICEF country programmes in South Asia, in development and humanitarian contexts.

description.narrative: Enhanced capacity building of staff and partners; effective gender integration and results across COVID19 Acceleration Results; strategic regional gender research, knowledge and evidence generation; and technical quality assurance and institutional effectiveness measures. Priority was placed on GBV, with capacity building and HAC programme development successfully completed. Education and Evaluation capacity building and technical resource finalized; PHC research (CHW) underway. ;Collaboration with cross sectors in ADAP, Climate Change and SP/Nutrition/B4R have been initiated with research, training packages, resources underway. ;Gender transformative programming, including focus on adolescent girl was strengethened with IDG202 SA challenge and initiation of RiGoR and RTE. | Status:Met | As-of Date:27/12/2021
